A provider is a plugin that lets Terraform interact with a specific cloud or service API. Each provider exposes resources and data sources you can manage.

Common DE providers:
- aws (Amazon Web Services)
- google (GCP)
- azurerm (Azure)
- snowflake (Snowflake data warehouse)
- databricks (Databricks)
- kubernetes (K8s)

Example configuration:
```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 5.0"
    }
    snowflake = {
      source  = "Snowflake-Labs/snowflake"
      version = "~> 0.87"
    }
  }
}

provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}
```

Key points:
- Always pin provider versions with ~> to avoid breaking changes
- Credentials come from env vars, AWS profiles, or IAM roles (never hardcode)
- Run 'terraform init' after adding a new provider to download it
